{"lemma":"زَهْوٌ","slug":"زَهْوٌ","root":"ز.ه.#","root_slug":"ز-ه-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-ه-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18340"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%87%D9%92%D9%88%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of زَهَا (zahā) (form I); bloom, florescence"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of زَهَا (zahā) (form I); date which begins to redden and ripen","examples":[{"text":"نَهَى رَسُولُ ٱللّٰهِ صَلَّى ٱللّٰهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ عَنِ الدُّبَّاءِ وَٱلْحَنْتَمِ وَٱلْمُزَفَّتِ وَٱلنَّقِيرِ وَأَنْ يُخْلَطَ الْبَلَحُ بِالزَّهْوِ.","english":"The prophet (PBUH) forbade [the preparation of wine in] a bottle-gourd, in a colocynth container, in a varnished jar, a hollow stump, and from mixing up ripe dates with nearly ripe dates."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of زَهَا (zahā) (form I); splendor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of زَهَا (zahā) (form I); beauty"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of زَهَا (zahā) (form I); pride"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of زَهَا (zahā) (form I); haughtiness, arrogance, conceit"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of زَهَا (zahā) (form I); vanity"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/zahw/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18340","headword_ar":"زَهْوٌ","root":"zhw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[is the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zahaA","text_ar":"زَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.): and also has the significations here following. ―         -b2- ]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pride"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as implying self-elevation]: (JK, S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vanity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain behaviour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boasting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glorying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrongdoing, injustice, injuriousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyranny."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A false,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain, saying;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATilN","text_ar":"بَاطِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K, and Ham p. 24;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lie,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falsehood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K, and Ham * ubi suprà;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an exaggeration in speech."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham ubi suprà.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAla zahowFA","text_ar":"قَالَ زَهْوًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He said a false,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain, saying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Ham ubi suprà.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A beautiful aspect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b5-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blossoms,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowers, of a plant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K.) ―         -b6-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brightness of a plant"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by its becoming red or yellow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuhuw~N","text_ar":"زُهُوٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euluw~N","text_ar":"عُلُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kAlz~ahowi","text_ar":"كالزَّهْوِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here put in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAlz~uhuw~i","text_ar":"كَالزُّهُوِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zahaA='N","text_ar":"زَهَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbN","text_ar":"سَحَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as the unrestricted mention of it requires, but in some of the copies of the K with damm [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuhaA='N","text_ar":"زُهَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b7-  Also, [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabaAtN zahowN","text_ar":"نَبَاتٌ زَهْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the TK,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A plant beautiful and bright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b8-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dates beginning to ripen"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busorN","text_ar":"بُسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that are becoming coloured"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulaw~inN","text_ar":"مُلَوِّنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (so in some copies of the S and K, and in the Mgh, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutalaw~inN","text_ar":"مُتَلَوِّنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which signifies the same], Har p. 416), or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that have become coloured"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulaw~anN","text_ar":"مُلَوَّنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"); (so in other copies of the S and K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuhuw~N","text_ar":"زُهُوٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euluw~N","text_ar":"عُلُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", thus in the handwriting of Az in the T: (TA:) [here, again, in the CK we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kAlz~ahowi","text_ar":"كالزَّهْوِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"put in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAlz~uhuw~i","text_ar":"كَالزُّهُوِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or perhaps it should be ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAlz~uhowi","text_ar":"كَالزُّهْوِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as appears from what follows in the next sentence:] in this sense,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zahowN","text_ar":"زَهْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n. used as a subst. (Mgh.) One says, when redness and yellowness appear in palm-trees,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado Zahara fiyhi Alz~ahowu","text_ar":"قَدْ ظَهَرَ فِيهِ الزَّهْوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dates becoming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become, red,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yellow, have appeared in them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Aln~axoli","text_ar":"فِى النَّخْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the people of El-Hijáz say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~uhowu","text_ar":"الزُّهْوُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm: (S:) [Fei says,] the subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zahaA Aln~axolu","text_ar":"زَهَا النَّخْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ the palm-trees showed redness and yellowness in their fruit ” is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alzhw","text_ar":"الزهو"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~uhowu","text_ar":"الزُّهْوُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"], with damm; and AHát says that this term is used only when the colour of the date has become free from admixture in redness or yellowness. (Msb.) ―         -b9-  You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN zahowN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ زَهْوٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A red and beautiful garment"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAbN zahowapN","text_ar":"ثِيَابٌ زَهْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAhiyapN","text_ar":"زَاهِيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red and beautiful garments"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (JK.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}